{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/bhyslop/projects/rbm_alpha_recipemuster","sessionId":"e299947d-b215-4936-9153-c5eae07b7553","version":"2.1.62","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"abc5127d858b2477b","slug":"zippy-wishing-star","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Slate 6 paces for heat ₣Aj using jjx_enroll. Use this exact pattern for each:\n\n```bash\ncat <<'DOCKET' | ./tt/vvw-r.RunVVX.sh jjx_enroll Aj --silks \"SILKS\"\nDESCRIPTION\nDOCKET\n```\n\nSlate these IN ORDER (each enroll commits, wait for each to complete before the next):\n\n1. silks: \"transform-jjs0-routines\"\nDescription: Transform JJS0-GallopsData.adoc: 4 axo_routine (load, save, persist, wrap) to axvo_procedure or axvo_method. Determine entity affiliation for each.\n\n2. silks: \"review-jjs0-interface-layer\"\nDescription: Review JJS0 interface terms: ~18 axi_cc_claudemd_verb, ~15 axi_cc_slash_command, ~25 axi_cli_subcommand, plus axa_cli_option/flag terms. Determine if these are affected by the new model or remain as-is.\n\n3. silks: \"verify-bus0-unaffected\"\nDescription: Verify BUS0-BashUtilitiesSpec.adoc uses only axo_entity and axrg_* regime voicings with no operation voicings needing transformation. Quick verification.\n\n4. silks: \"rewrite-completeness-checklists\"\nDescription: Replace Procedure/Command/Guide/Lifecycle Documentation Completeness sections in AXLA with new checklists based on axvo_procedure, axvo_method, axvo_group, and axho_* markers.\n\n5. silks: \"delete-legacy-terms\"\nDescription: Remove all deprecated terms listed in AXLA deprecation appendix. Remove the deprecation appendix itself. Remove legacy Procedure Hierarchy section and old completeness checklists. Verify no remaining references to deleted terms across all specs.\n\n6. silks: \"note-future-heat-bottle-ops\"\nDescription: The mkr_*, opss_*, opbs_*, opbr_*, scr_* operations in RBS0 (bottle, network, sentry, security) have non-rbtgo prefixes and were out of scope. Slate an itch or create a note for a future heat to bring them up to standards established in this heat.\n\nAfter all 6, report the coronets assigned."},"uuid":"fc71d020-c7b9-46b1-b0a2-ed4da86a216e","timestamp":"2026-02-27T18:57:49.754Z"}
